JO  - AMR
SP  - 527
EP  - 539
VL  - 10
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Vicarious learning and modeling are important processes in the acquisition, development, and alteration of behavior in organizations. The authors argue that a primary basis for vicarious learning is a cognitively held ?script? on the part of the observer of a model. A script is a procedural knowledge structure or schema for understanding and enacting behaviors. The close parallels are drawn between scripts and vicarious learning as vehicles for both understanding and influencing organizational behavior.
AB  - Vicarious learning and modeling are important processes in the acquisition, development, and alteration of behavior in organizations. The authors argue that a primary basis for vicarious learning is a cognitively held ?script? on the part of the observer of a model. A script is a procedural knowledge structure or schema for understanding and enacting behaviors. The close parallels are drawn between scripts and vicarious learning as vehicles for both understanding and influencing organizational behavior.
